column5: Just one of those days that goes right. First warm day of the year, and it sure was, provided we kept out of the wind. Good times. We caught all sorts of panfish, and all decent fish. No giants, but crappies in the 10-11" range like nothing, 8" bluegills were an annoyance, and the odd perch came to visit. Awesome day on some protected little pits to kick off spring.
Nice day, but man was the wind crazy up here today.
Nice! I spent the day shopping for appliances.
Looks like a good start to spring!
Another spring crappie report. Good stuff Nice Black Crappies!
